{"/service/ndnp/wa/batch_wa_canvasback_ver02/data/sn87093436/00200291463/1948110101/0119.xml":{"full_text":"THE SCANDINAVIAN AMERICAN\nEvidence 0f Glacial Period\n0n Hawaii, Scientist Discovers\nSTOCKHOLM, Oct. 15. (By\nairmail) Evidence of a glacial\nperiod on the Hawaiian Islands,\nalmost coincidental with the great\nclimatic recession in northern Eur\nope, has been discovered by a Swe\ndish scientist, D\u2018r, Olof H. Selling.\nHe recently presented a thesis at\nthe University of Stockholm, deal\ning with the evolution of vegetable\nlife on Hawaii during the past ten\nthousand years. In 1938 he was\na member of an expedition to\nthose parts headed by Prof. C.\nSkottsberg. during which sample\nseries of peat deposits were col\nlected. These now form the base\nmaterial for his thesis.\nDr. Selling\"s research has\nthrown light on a hitherto com\npletely unknown Chapter in the\nhistory of the Central Pacific.\nThe most notable result of the in\nvestigation is the discovery of a\nclose similarity between the Vege\ntative evolution of Hawaii and\nthat of New Zealand, America. and\nEurope. This gives support to the\nNews In Brief\nOne Bemadotte succeeds anoth.\ner as chief of the Swedish Boy\nScouts. Lennart Bernadotte, only\nson of Prince Wilhelm, has been\nnamed head of the Scout union af\nter the late Count Folke Berna\ndotte. At the same time, Countess\nEstelle Bernadotte, Count Folke's\nwidow; who was Miss Estelle Man\nville, of Pleasantville. N. Y.. was\nawai-ded the Golden Lily, the hon\nor insignia of the Scouts. Mr. Len\nnart Bernadette. a grand-son of\nKing Gustaf\u201c. has long been ac\ntive in the Boy Scout movement\nin Sweden as well as in other ath\nletic and philanthropic activities.\nHe is an expert cameraman. hav\ning written and directed a number\nof educational film shorts.\nArctic Explorer\nVisiting U. S. A.\nPETER FREUCHEN, 62. the fa\nmous Arctic Explorer. as he re\nturned from a five months investi\ngation o! Greenland, on board the\nGdynia America Line motor-ship\n\u201cBatory\u201d which arrived Nov. 6\nfrom Southampton. Copenhagen\nand Gdynia with a capacity sail\u2014\ning list of 894 passengers. Mr.\nFreuchen accompanied Denmark\u2018s\nPrime Minister Hans Hedtoft to\nGreenland to arrange for the in\ntroduction of reindeer to the Arc\ntic subcontinent as a Source of\nmeat supply to Greenlanders who\nhave been subsisting on an ex\nclusively fish diet. After studying\u2018\nclimatic conditions Mr. Freuchen!\ndecided that only Alaskan rein-i\ndeer. not the Lapland species.i\ncould thrive in Gremland.\nHe is returnlng to negotiate with\nour Department of the Interior lo\nxly a herd of Alaskan reindeer by\nplane: to Greenland in exchange\nfor exclusive American rights of\nhunting mulkox which he: (or\n.Vem been forbidden in Greenland.\nMr. Men. who is one o! the\nworld's Authorities on weether.\n\u201c\ufb01lled the! Greenland. as Well as\nNorms. Men end Scoumd were\nbeau-acme due to the re-\nW\u2018Mmfm'\ufb02orth Arctic\nview that climatic developments\nfollowing the glacial period have\nrun a similar course all over the\nglobe, probably deriving from vario\nations in solar energy.\nDental Drill\nlessens Pain\nSTOCKHOLM. Dentists as\nwell as their patients will\u2018 probably\nbe pleased to hear about a new\ntype of dental drills developed by\na Swedish firm, A B Dentatus.\nMade from Coromant, a tungsten\n\"carbide .alloy produced by the\nlSandviken Steel Works, these\n\u2018drills make the treatment quicker\n'and less painful, keeping their cut\u00bb\niting edges many times longer than\nlthose of ordinary steel drills. Dur\ning a recent test one single hard\u2014\nmetal drill removed 1.38 grams\nof dental substance in 45 minutes,\nwhereas no less than 48 ordinary\nEsteel' drills and 69 minutes were\nrequired to grind away 0.89\ngrams of the same substance.\nHard metal, however, is not used\nfor the entire drill, which in such\na case would break into pieces\n'from the vibration: but only for\n[the point. After the hard metal\nIhas been welded onto the stem of\nlthe drill according to a special\nImethod the cutting edges are\nIground out by means of a diamond\n\u2018wheel,\nThe hard-metal drills have at\nitracted considerable attention\nabroad, and one of the largest\n\u2018American manufacturers of dental\n{equipment has recently required\n:8. manufacturing license for the U.\nis. A. The same American firm\u2018\nalso produces another \u2018Dentatusl\nspeciality: dentists' grinding\u2018\nwheels having diamond powder as\nabrasive agent instead of emery.\nThis product was developed in the\nlate 1930's; the 'war interfered\nwith sales abroad. but the diamond\nwheels proved an. invaluable asset\nto Swedish dentists. After the\nwar. Dentatus has become one of\nthe leading suppliers of diamond\nwheels on the European market.\nIn its modern plant in a suburb\nof Stockholm. the Dentatus fac\ntory produces practically every\nthing a dentist might need: drills\nand grinding tools. probes and\nmortars, lamps and dentist\u2019s chairs.\netc. I\nGreat attention is given to the\nscientific testing of instruments\nand equipment. A dental drill. to\nquote one example. can be ruined\nin ten seconds when in inexper\nienced hands, as the result of sud\u2014\nden overheating. Hence the heat\ning process is studied by the ex\u2014\nperts of the Dentatus Co. by\nmeans of test drilling of animal\nteeth. with special instruments\nkeeping pressure and number of\nrewlutions at a constant level\nwhile other instruments register\nthe heat development.\nA Scandinavian scientific sta\n\u2018tion may be established in Kenya.\nBritish East Africa. A commit\nltee has been formed for a more\njdetailed planning, consisting of\n\u2018Swedish. Danish. and Norwegian\nscientists. The project. which was\ndiscussed at a recent meeting in\nCopenhagen. has aroused great in\nterest in the Scandinavian colony\nin Kenya. which has pronounced\nitself ready to raise the neces\nsary funds. The work at the sta\ntion will include research into lim\nnologiml. glaciological. and oth\nor biological problems, as well as\nagriculture.\nFAIRWAY GOLF\nSTUDIO RANGE\nV. KLlT\u2018I\u2018E, PROFESSIONAL\nlmpuw Your Gum- By Practice\nLESSONS IF 01313:!)\nFull Uni of Golf Clubs sad\nAccessories for Sula\n1!\u201c: Anton Run-ruin 2.\u201c\nsum:\nFinnish Paperexporier Home\nAfter U. S. Business Trip\n.Mr. Holger R. Sumellus. manager of the Finnish Papermilis Asp\nsoeiation, together with Mrs. Sumelius. sailed in the Swedish Am\neriean liner \u201cStockholm\" last Monday. Mr. Sumelius has been here\nnegotiating with the large American newspapers to supply them\nwith paper from Finnish mills and upon his return home he de\nclared that he was very satisfied with the results of his trip.\nTemperance Committee Wants:\nI9Ab9|i\u00a7hmquuorRationing\nSTOCKHOLM. The 1944 Tem.\u2019\nperance Committee has recom\nmended that the present system of\nrationing be abolished. and that\nthe sale of wines and spirits be\nfreed. At the same time. the care\nof alcoholics should be made more\neffective and the temperance prop-\nKARL'S\nSHOE STORE\n116 Bike St.\n1303 Second Ave.\nSEATTLE\nThe Alice Shoppe\nLADIES' APPAREL\nNOVELTIES\n902 E. 65th KEnwmd 9632\nR. E. SULLIVAN\nSince I902\n\u2018IGA RS (\u2018ON I-\u2018ECTIONS\nMAGAZINES\nBARBER SHOP\nloot; l'nlon House 1.506 ls! Aw.\nSEATTLE\nNEW STUDEBAKER\nTRUCKS\n\u201cToughest Trucks\non the Road\"\nL E. Belcourt Co.\nsn'nnumn CARS\n12th and Hm- Cattle\naganda intensified. A majoritvy of\nthe Committee suggests however.\nthat the restrictions on the sale\nof alcoholic beverages in restau\nrants and hotels be retained, while\na minority prefers a continuation\nof the present so-called Bratt Sys\ntem. with a few modifications. It\nis primarily the temperance move\u2014\nment people who advocate the abo\nlition of the system now in force.\nGroelings and Best Wishes\nEMARD PACKING COMPANY\n61.\") Lowman Building\nC. B. BALLARD AND SON\nNASH SALES and SERVICE\